Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.11,0:00:02.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,During the war to protect Frianno Castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.07,0:00:05.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the young hero summoned by the \Nprincess brought victory to her country.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.65,0:00:10.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is that the hero found out that he couldn't return to his homeworld...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.11,0:00:12.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...even after all that passionate fighting on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.44,0:00:14.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must be really troubled now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.63,0:00:16.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then again, at a time like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.28,0:00:19.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...allow me, Ricotta Elmar, to help you think of a solution!{ellipses due to different speakers continuing the same sentences}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.09,0:02:12.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The war has ended!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.48,0:02:20.45,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur4\fad(500,0)\pos(470,278)}  「I want to go home! But I can't? {\blur4\fad(500,0)\pos(163,395)} {AL: lol.. i cannot decide which to use.. tell me what you think. just copy paste each over another and you'll see the difference}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.48,0:02:20.45,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur4\fad(500,0)\pos(431,318)} Sir Hero in Flonyard!」 {\blur4\fad(500,0)\pos(124,435)}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.93,0:02:19.00,Next Episode Dialogues,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Since neither side was able to defeat the other, we've decided the outcome using points,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:22.03,Next Episode Dialogues,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and Biscotti was able to win by defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.94,0:02:30.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, after this, we'll invite Biscotti's Leader of Knights, Laurent, to talk about this round's battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.16,0:02:32.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Laurent, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.68,0:02:33.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.88,0:02:35.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And, Captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:41.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if possible, we would also like to interview the hero about his gorgeous debut!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.87,0:02:45.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-About the hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.69,0:02:48.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we had planned for him to take a break,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.19,0:02:50.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so, at the moment, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.19,0:02:51.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That information is classified?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.83,0:02:53.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:57.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, we'll ask you all our questions later!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.34,0:02:59.08,Dialogue Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Wise move, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.19,0:02:59.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.77,0:03:01.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.90,0:03:04.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't leave this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.26,0:03:06.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way we can present a hero like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.33,0:03:10.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.32,0:03:13.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Hero won't be able to go back to his homeworld!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.93,0:03:16.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like he is really depressed about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.58,0:03:20.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.51,0:03:24.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That being said, Princess, you also have responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.75,0:03:27.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Amelita...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.87,0:03:30.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First off, you need to give a speech\Naddressing the soldiers of both countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:33.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, there is the cease-fire with her Highness, Leo,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.36,0:03:35.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the interview for our victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.55,0:03:38.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and thanking the organizations for their sponsorship.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.50,0:03:44.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all of that, you need to practice for your musical performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.97,0:03:50.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, at least for today, we'll need to leave the issue of Sir Hero to the research team.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.08,0:03:52.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.47,0:03:55.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, this sort of matter is the specialty of{alumni is plural. Anyway, using "alumna" (since Elmar is female) is not proper here as it implies Elmar graduated from the princess, which is obviously wrong. I replaced it with "chief researcher" as that was her title given by Wikipedia. Moved to next line anyway to improve sentence structure. -Anigel}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.45,0:03:59.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief Researcher Elmar, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:04.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to find a way to help the \Nsummoned Hero return to his homeworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.99,0:04:09.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I didn't stop the Princess from summoning him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.63,0:04:11.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I didn't really confirm things first,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.73,0:04:14.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this is my responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.54,0:04:17.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to see the Princess looking sad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.47,0:04:34.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.78,0:04:37.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this is a different world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:42.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. It's your fault for not preparing \Nyourself when you answered the summoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.17,0:04:42.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Preparing myself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.88,0:04:45.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What preparation?! It's all because of this dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.00,0:04:49.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just jumping down to the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:51.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when a hole in the ground suddenly opened!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:04:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsumaki opened a hole in the ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.11,0:05:02.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.47,0:05:04.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Welcome to Flonyard.{She's reading it, so the entire spiel is in quotes. Not individual quotes for every line, but quotes for the whole thing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:06.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come to Biscotti.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.66,0:05:16.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Attention: This is a summon for a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.74,0:05:18.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you are summoned, there is no turning back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.73,0:05:23.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to refuse, do not touch this crest."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.57,0:05:27.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell I'd understand that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.95,0:05:30.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's none of my business! Don't complain to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.45,0:05:34.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the research team is searching for a way to help you return home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:36.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They should come up with a solution soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.10,0:05:40.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be great if they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.66,0:05:43.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway. Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.97,0:05:46.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,although you're a fool, you'll be receiving VIP treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.80,0:05:49.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't let you suffer during your stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:51.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just accept this for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.41,0:05:53.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this money?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.09,0:05:55.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, wait, I don't think money...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.16,0:05:58.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your reward for actively participating on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.06,0:06:02.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you refuse to accept it, it'll be difficult for the agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.33,0:06:11.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Although many of the soldiers took part in the war for fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.95,0:06:13.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the compensation paid
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.69,0:06:17.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is heavily based on how much one contributes to the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.48,0:06:22.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They would like to at least get their participation fees back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.39,0:06:23.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Participation fees?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.95,0:06:30.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh boy, I guess I need to start with the basics for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.26,0:06:55.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though war is a way for countries to negotiate,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:06:58.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,at the same time it also allows countries and organizations to hold activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.93,0:07:01.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Although we fought against Galette this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.76,0:07:06.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there are smaller scale battles, like civil wars, between villages and associations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.69,0:07:11.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are fighting matches in villages similar to festivals?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.86,0:07:16.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess you could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.21,0:07:19.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When the time comes to decide on war,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.98,0:07:23.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the person in charge collects participation fees from those who are taking part,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.71,0:07:27.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,taking into account the wealth{amount} of both countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.59,0:07:33.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the war takes place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.02,0:07:35.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The winning country takes 60 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.22,0:07:38.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The losing country takes the remaining 40 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.52,0:07:42.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ratio according to the continental agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.85,0:07:49.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At least half of the cash collected is given to the participating soldiers as their reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.14,0:07:52.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This ratio is also part of the continental agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.87,0:07:57.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the remaining half will be used to sponsor national engineering that will help the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.08,0:07:58.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,such as building hospitals
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.25,0:08:01.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,building a fortress,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.12,0:08:04.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,financially supporting government servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.92,0:08:07.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or used to protect the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.12,0:08:13.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, um, how should I say this. Real wars,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.49,0:08:19.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when some go against the continental agreement, or those wars where people actually die...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:24.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We used to have that kind of war in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:27.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially in our battles with monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:31.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason why we can end our wars without any injuries
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:35.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is all thanks to the power of Flonyard that is hidden underneath the battlefield grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.99,0:08:40.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides those places, not only can people get hurt, they even die.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.59,0:08:43.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, exactly how big is the protected area?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.84,0:08:48.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually our country, city, and fortress are all built where the protective power is strongest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.99,0:08:52.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are many dangerous places on the main roads and the sides of mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.60,0:08:56.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,especially from those huge, dangerous, \Nand ferocious animals on the main road.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.78,0:09:01.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you add in the team that travels for war,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.17,0:09:04.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you actually have the advantage of a safer journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.73,0:09:06.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.77,0:09:09.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't seem to know anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.62,0:09:14.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's head over to Rico's first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.99,0:09:18.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps they have made some progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.43,0:09:25.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.19,0:09:30.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Ricotta Elmar, have been trying very hard to find a way for you to return,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.96,0:09:32.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but to no avail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.24,0:09:34.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, we'll do whatever we{\fscx230}-{She was cut off. Ellipses aren't the right punctuation for that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:36.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Rico, please calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.18,0:09:39.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The hero and I did not expect a solution so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.45,0:09:42.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.31,0:09:44.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Uh, y-yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:47.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?{Only the first letter is repeated for a stutter except in the case of "Wh" and "Th" etc.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.48,0:09:50.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You did say something about a deadline?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.18,0:09:51.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.53,0:09:54.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, three days before spring break ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.77,0:09:58.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I need to be home a day before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.49,0:09:59.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have sixteen days left until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:01.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixteen days?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.17,0:10:04.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I should be able to get a solution by then!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.44,0:10:05.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.71,0:10:10.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But before that,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:17.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if I go to the place where I was summoned, would I be able to get a signal?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.73,0:10:21.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Signal?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.55,0:10:28.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I really can't get through!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.63,0:10:33.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.33,0:10:36.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Life is all about challenges!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.40,0:10:38.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Never give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.29,0:10:42.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Hero, it's been prepared!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.66,0:10:44.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what has?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.74,0:10:49.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is used for reporting. It's a machine that can greatly increase Flonyard's frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.37,0:10:53.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was something I invented when I was five,{Argh! "Although" and "but" aren't used in the same sentence in English =P}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.32,0:10:56.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but right now the entire mainland is using it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:01.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Try it, Sir Hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.76,0:11:11.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a signal!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.28,0:11:13.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! Ricotta, you're really fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.56,0:11:15.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the compliment!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.83,0:11:17.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really touched!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.34,0:11:19.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.43,0:11:49.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:50.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got through!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.95,0:11:52.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.92,0:11:55.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Hey, Sink?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:57.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your voice seems kind of distant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.57,0:11:59.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you now? At the airport?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.30,0:12:01.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, yeah... sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.95,0:12:04.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, have you read my mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.01,0:12:06.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My papa won't be able to go because of work,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.28,0:12:09.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but Mama and I will still be able to go on vacation with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.16,0:12:12.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.66,0:12:16.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mama said she's looking forward to the flower viewing. She hasn't done that in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.11,0:12:19.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sink, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.87,0:12:21.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you feeling sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.20,0:12:25.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why? I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.47,0:12:27.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.36,0:12:32.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, there's something wrong with my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.01,0:12:35.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a while before I can contact you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.92,0:12:41.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just calling you to let you know that I'm doing fine, so don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.13,0:12:43.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.40,0:12:45.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't worry then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.08,0:12:52.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it becomes hard for you to contact people,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.57,0:12:56.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,make sure you call your uncle, aunt, and Nanami, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.51,0:12:58.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone will be worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.55,0:13:01.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. That won't be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.47,0:13:06.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.54,0:13:10.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Ricotta.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.05,0:13:12.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible to keep the signal running for a little longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.51,0:13:15.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I still have other people that I'd like to contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.33,0:13:17.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.19,0:13:18.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Sir Hero...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.44,0:13:25.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if possible, would you let me take \Na look at that gadget you call a phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.93,0:13:30.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just take it apart and look at its internal structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.45,0:13:36.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get very excited whenever I meet new, unknown gadgets!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.04,0:13:37.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way, no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.87,0:13:41.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guarantee I'll return it to you in one piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:43.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you take it apart, I'll lose the warranty!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.76,0:13:47.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! I guarantee it'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.72,0:13:51.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not about your guarantee, \Nit's about the manufacturer's warranty!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.71,0:13:51.76,Dialogue Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.82,0:13:57.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Sir Hero managed to get in touch with his hometown?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.52,0:14:01.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The hero and Ricotta seem at ease now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.87,0:14:05.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The hero has also agreed to stay during this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.37,0:14:09.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That includes participating in war-related activities and to live positively.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.30,0:14:13.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. I'll report it to the princess right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.06,0:14:14.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:16.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.25,0:14:17.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.24,0:14:21.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady d'Arquien and Yukikaze might be\Nreturning from their travel within two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.63,0:14:24.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's exciting to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.41,0:14:26.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eclair, is there some good news?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.86,0:14:29.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady d'Arquien is coming back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.01,0:14:31.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.09,0:14:33.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means Yuki's coming too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.12,0:14:33.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.87,0:14:35.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.30,0:14:37.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Biscotti's most powerful knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:40.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady d'Arquien and our friend, Yukikaze!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.31,0:14:43.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them are very trustworthy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.10,0:14:49.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's a rare sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:51.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Soil God!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.72,0:14:53.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Soil God?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.12,0:14:55.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You really know nothing at all, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.70,0:14:58.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the spiritual creature that lives within the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.81,0:15:04.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Soil God appearing here shows that the land here is rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.32,0:15:08.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.46,0:15:13.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Sir Hero is with Ricotta and Eclair right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.19,0:15:14.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're happily exploring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.02,0:15:17.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And he'll also come to your concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.54,0:15:22.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great. Are Sir Hero, Ricotta and Eclair getting along well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.69,0:15:25.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From what I know, they already are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.64,0:15:29.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I still can't completely relax,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.85,0:15:31.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but at least I can heave a sigh of relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.19,0:15:36.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess, you worry too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.37,0:15:39.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am who I am today thanks to everyone's support.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.04,0:15:42.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to do my best for the things that I'm capable of doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.96,0:15:44.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, Leader of Knights,{change to leader of knights or something similar}{so why wasn't it changed already?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.75,0:15:46.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess, it's about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.88,0:15:48.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.63,0:15:54.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I must really apologize to Sir Hero after this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.21,0:15:58.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I need to tell him that he did really well in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.47,0:16:02.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I could pet Sir Hero's head?{to brush gently; to stroke; to caress;}{AL: i can't find a suitable word for this... she's just trying to compliment him by physical contact i think}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.84,0:16:04.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that wouldn't be disrespectful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.76,0:16:08.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I also need to compliment Eclair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.00,0:16:10.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She fought hard this round.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.65,0:16:13.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'll also do my best in my concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.57,0:16:19.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I need to write a letter to Princess Leo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.20,0:16:25.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why Princess Leo has \Ngrown so fond of war these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.20,0:16:31.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She used to really praise my singing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:34.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so why does she no longer listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.70,0:16:42.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Leo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.23,0:16:44.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you won't be attending
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.71,0:16:46.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Millhiore's concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.44,0:16:48.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As if I would go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.41,0:16:50.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in listening to the doggie princess's singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.08,0:16:53.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.48,0:16:57.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we go mess around then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.94,0:17:01.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The defeated country messing up the winning country's banquet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.70,0:17:03.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell I'll do something so shameful!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.59,0:17:08.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, then drink as you please tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.23,0:17:11.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That was my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.30,0:17:11.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.95,0:17:13.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, how's Gaul?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.27,0:17:16.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I ordered him to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.39,0:17:18.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.07,0:17:26.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since my sister lost, it must mean \Nthat the hero is kind of tough, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.44,0:17:27.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.64,0:17:29.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a hyperactive kind of warrior,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.73,0:17:31.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a lot like Sir Gaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.36,0:17:35.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's interesting. I'm not gonna take revenge for my sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.39,0:17:37.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I guess I'll just go have some fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.62,0:17:45.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you attend the Princess's concert \Nsmelling all sweaty, we'll be in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.02,0:17:48.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a shower before you go to the concert!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.48,0:17:49.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where should I take my shower?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.82,0:17:51.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You could ask for directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.86,0:17:54.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll know if you ask the people inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.05,0:18:01.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, there's no one here, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:05.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone busily preparing for the concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.01,0:18:07.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the bathroom anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.45,0:18:09.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! That should be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.69,0:18:16.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A changing room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.61,0:18:18.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I made it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:22.41,Location Names,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(390,400)\fad(500,0)}「 The Bathing Place
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:22.41,Location Names,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(425,425)\fad(500,0)} Currently reserved for women 」
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.99,0:18:25.41,Location Names 2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(310,107)\fad(500,0)}「 Currently occupied by Millhiore 」
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.41,0:18:26.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.48,0:18:29.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's open to the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.45,0:18:39.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Did someone get here first?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.33,0:18:57.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.00,0:19:14.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see it! I didn't see anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.75,0:19:16.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I am so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.06,0:19:18.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's disrespectful for me to behave like this in front of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.26,0:19:19.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, no, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.55,0:19:22.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought someone was here, but I didn't know it was the princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.87,0:19:23.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.83,0:19:26.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Hero?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.34,0:19:30.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.54,0:19:35.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't normally come to this shared bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.52,0:19:37.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only at this kind of time, I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.47,0:19:40.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um, I will leave at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.15,0:19:42.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Hero, please do enjoy yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.19,0:19:56.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Sir Hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:19:58.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.38,0:20:02.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have so much to talk to you about,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.28,0:20:05.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,like the summoning issue and the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.68,0:20:08.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, after the concert ends,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:11.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,could I have some of your time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.40,0:20:13.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Ah, yeah! That won't be a problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:16.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.22,0:20:17.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, I'll see you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.94,0:20:19.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.82,0:20:32.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have asked her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.30,0:20:34.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect this to be reserved for women.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.87,0:20:37.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It... shouldn't be, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.40,0:20:40.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.93,0:20:54.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We are the Galette Lion Army!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.84,0:20:59.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From Sir Gaul's Secret Intelligence Unit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.40,0:21:02.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Genoise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.68,0:21:04.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.85,0:21:05.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.70,0:21:07.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Biscotti's Sir Hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.56,0:21:12.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be kidnapping your important princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.76,0:21:17.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be waiting for you at Myon Castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:22.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still a minute and a half until the Princess's concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.03,0:21:23.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you save her?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.09,0:21:27.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, we're ignoring the continental agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.93,0:21:31.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be holding a battle to take back the abducted princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.50,0:21:34.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have an army of 200 soldiers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.73,0:21:36.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,an elite force that is led by Sir Gaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.64,0:21:41.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Gaul requests a one-on-one fight with the hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.98,0:21:45.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the hero declines, we don't know what will happen to the princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.74,0:21:50.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'll accept!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.40,0:21:54.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've answered the princess's call!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.98,0:21:57.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Biscotti's Hero, Sink!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.59,0:22:02.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter who and where you're from, I'll fight you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.66,0:23:53.38,Next Episode Dialogues,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Nyah! Sir Hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.38,0:23:55.15,Next Episode Dialogues,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Rico, please do your part.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.15,0:23:57.57,Next Episode Dialogues,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}All right! I'll do my best in the next episode too!
